cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, specifically in the area of reading comprehension. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of BERT, a popular deep learning model, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analysis of factors that contribute to generalization and transfer, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of multiple datasets and the proposal of a new model suggest that it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
